Package: scRoPE
Type: Package
Title: scRoPE: Robust Differential Analysis for Single-Cell RNA-seq
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-04-09
Authors@R: person("Lehang", "Zhong", email = "lehang.zhong@mail.utoronto.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Lehang Zhong [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Lehang Zhong <lehang.zhong@mail.utoronto.ca>
Description: Provides robust inference for negative binomial mixed models in
    multi-donor single-cell RNA-seq studies. scRoPE builds on the NEBULA
    framework (He et al., 2021, <doi:10.1038/s42003-021-02146-6>) by combining
    large-sample (LN) and hierarchical-likelihood (HL) fits with Godambe
    (sandwich) information to deliver robustly adjusted Wald, Score, and scaled
    likelihood-ratio tests for linear contrasts. These adjustments enable
    reliable differential and co-expression analysis under variance
    misspecification.
